-- Nomura Hires Bob Janjuah, Kevin Gaynor for Cross-Asset Allocation Strategy
-- B y   M a t t h e w   B r o w n
-- 2010-10-06T08:09:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-06/nomura-hires-bob-janjuah-kevin-gaynor-for-cross-asset-allocation-strategy.html
Nomura International Plc. hired Bob Janjuah  and  Kevin Gaynor  as co-heads of cross-asset allocation
strategy and  Geoff Kendrick  as group of 10 foreign-exchange
strategist.  “Their hiring is consistent with the overall strategic
plan for our business,” New York-based  Michael Guarnieri ,
global head of fixed-income research at Nomura in New York, said
in an e-mailed statement. “Nomura’s global fixed income
research team now numbers over 180 client-facing research
analysts in the Americas, Europe, Asia and Japan.”  Gaynor, Janjuah and Kendrick will all be based in London,
Nomura said.  Janjuah was previously at Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc
where he was chief market strategist and co-head of the bank’s
global macro strategy unit, Nomura said. Gaynor also joins from
RBS, where he was chief markets economist.  Kendrick was formerly executive director and currency
strategist at UBS AG in London.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Matthew Brown in London at 
